{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864045754,"sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","part":{"id":"prt_d79bedc70001aQmTAg1uvwPmhN","messageID":"msg_d79bed5bc001y0cRC9ITHwAisc","sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1d0a5100e2a446ff96612d66","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: The K8s/AgentCube Provider delivers a complete developer toolchain for AI agent lifecycle management on Kubernetes. It consists of three components:\n8: \n9: 1. **CLI Toolkit** (`kubectl-agentcube`) — Command-line interface for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube CRDs or standard Kubernetes deployments.\n10: 2. **Client-Go Library** — Generated Kubernetes typed client for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n11: 3. **Python SDK** (`agentcube-sdk`) — High-level Python client library for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n12: \n13: ### 1.2 System Architecture\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                          Developer Workstation                           │\n18: │                                                                          │\n19: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────┐  │\n20: │  │  CLI Toolkit     │  │   Python SDK     │  │    client-go (Go)     │  │\n21: │  │  (Typer/Python)  │  │  (requests)      │  │  (k8s.io/client-go)   │  │\n22: │  │                  │  │                  │  │                       │  │\n23: │  │  pack/build/     │  │  CodeInterpreter │  │  AgentRuntime         │  │\n24: │  │  publish/invoke/ │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  CodeInterpreter      │  │\n25: │  │  status          │  │  clients         │  │  typed clients        │  │\n26: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────┬───────────┘  │\n27: │           │                     │                        │              │\n28: └───────────┼─────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────┘\n29:             │                     │                        │\n30:             ▼                     ▼                        ▼\n31: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n32: │                        Kubernetes Cluster                                │\n33: │                                                                          │\n34: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n35: │  │  AgentRuntime CRD   │    │  Standard K8s Resources               │   │\n36: │  │  (volcano.sh)       │    │                                       │   │\n37: │  │                     │    │  Deployment + NodePort Service        │   │\n38: │  │  AgentRuntime       │    │  (provider=k8s mode)                  │   │\n39: │  │  CodeInterpreter    │    │                                       │   │\n40: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └───────────────────┬───────────────────┘   │\n41: │             │                                   │                       │\n42: │             ▼                                   ▼                       │\n43: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n44: │  │  Workload Manager   │    │  Router                               │   │\n45: │  │  (Control Plane)    │    │  (Data Plane)                         │   │\n46: │  │                     │    │                                       │   │\n47: │  │  Session creation   │    │  /v1/namespaces/{ns}/                 │   │\n48: │  │  Session deletion   │    │    agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/ │   │\n49: │  │                     │    │    code-interpreters/{name}/invoc/    │   │\n50: │  └─────────────────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ### 1.3 Component Relationships\n55: \n56: ```\n57: CLI Toolkit\n58: ├── Runtime Layer (orchestration)\n59: │   ├── PackRuntime     → validates workspace, generates Dockerfile, saves metadata\n60: │   ├── BuildRuntime    → builds container images (local Docker or cloud)\n61: │   ├── PublishRuntime  → deploys to K8s (AgentRuntime CR or Deployment+Service)\n62: │   ├── InvokeRuntime   → POSTs to agent endpoint with session management\n63: │   └── StatusRuntime   → reads and displays agent status\n64: │\n65: ├── Service Layer (infrastructure)\n66: │   ├── MetadataService    → load/save/validate agent_metadata.yaml\n67: │   ├── DockerService      → Docker SDK operations (build, push, login, remove)\n68: │   ├── KubernetesProvider → standard K8s Deployment + Service management\n69: │   └── AgentCubeProvider  → AgentRuntime CRD management via CustomObjects API\n70: │\n71: └── Model Layer (data structures)\n72:     ├── AgentMetadata      → Pydantic model for agent configuration\n73:     └── MetadataOptions    → dataclass for CLI option parsing\n74: \n75: Python SDK\n76: ├── High-Level Clients\n77: │   ├── CodeInterpreterClient → context manager, session lifecycle, file/command ops\n78: │   └── AgentRuntimeClient    → context manager, invoke with session bootstrap\n79: │\n80: ├── Low-Level Clients\n81: │   ├── ControlPlaneClient          → Workload Manager HTTP (create/delete session)\n82: │   ├── CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient → Router HTTP (execute, files)\n83: │   └── AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient    → Router HTTP (invoke)\n84: │\n85: └── Utilities\n86:     ├── http.py      → create_session (requests.Session with HTTPAdapter)\n87:     ├── utils.py     → read_token_from_file (SA token)\n88:     └── log.py       → get_logger\n89: \n90: client-go\n91: ├── Clientset          → versioned.Interface, RuntimeV1alpha1()\n92: ├── Typed Clients      → AgentRuntimeInterface, CodeInterpreterInterface\n93: ├── Informers          → SharedInformerFactory, per-type informers\n94: ├── Listers            → AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister\n95: └── Fake Clients       → in-memory test doubles\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### 1.4 Package Layouts\n99: \n100: #### CLI Toolkit (`cmd/cli/`)\n101: \n102: ```\n103: cmd/cli/\n104: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Project metadata, dependencies, entry points\n105: ├── agentcube/\n106: │   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, exports: app, PackRuntime, BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime\n107: │   ├── cli/\n108: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n109: │   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\n110: │   ├── models/\n111: │   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n112: │   ├── runtime/\n113: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n114: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            — PackRuntime\n115: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py           — BuildRuntime\n116: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         — PublishRuntime\n117: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          — InvokeRuntime\n118: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          — StatusRuntime\n119: │   ├── services/\n120: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n121: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n122: │   │   ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService\n123: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider\n124: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider\n125: │   └── operations/\n126: │       └── __init__.py                — Placeholder module docstring (no symbols)\n127: └── examples/\n128:     ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n129:     └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n130: ```\n131: \n132: #### Python SDK (`sdk-python/`)\n133: \n134: ```\n135: sdk-python/\n136: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Package agentcube-sdk, dependencies\n137: ├── agentcube/\n138: │   ├── __init__.py                    — Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n139: │   ├── code_interpreter.py            — CodeInterpreterClient\n140: │   ├── agent_runtime.py               — AgentRuntimeClient\n141: │   ├── exceptions.py                  — Exception classes\n142: │   ├── clients/\n143: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports client classes\n144: │   │   ├── control_plane.py           — ControlPlaneClient\n145: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n146: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n147: │   └── utils/\n148: │       ├── __init__.py                — Empty (module marker)\n149: │       ├── http.py                    — create_session\n150: │       ├── utils.py                   — read_token_from_file\n151: │       └── log.py                     — get_logger\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### client-go (`client-go/`)\n155: \n156: ```\n157: client-go/\n158: ├── clientset/\n159: │   └── versioned/\n160: │       ├── clientset.go               — Clientset, Interface, constructors\n161: │       ├── scheme/\n162: │       │   ├── register.go            — Scheme / codecs\n163: │       │   └── doc.go\n164: │       ├── fake/\n165: │       │   ├── clientset_generated.go — Fake clientset\n166: │       │   ├── register.go\n167: │       │   └── doc.go\n168: │       └── typed/runtime/v1alpha1/\n169: │           ├── runtime_client.go      — RuntimeV1alpha1Client, Interface\n170: │           ├── agentruntime.go        — AgentRuntimeInterface\n171: │           ├── codeinterpreter.go     — CodeInterpreterInterface\n172: │           ├── generated_expansion.go — Expansion interfaces\n173: │           ├── doc.go\n174: │           └── fake/\n175: │               ├── fake_runtime_client.go\n176: │               ├── fake_agentruntime.go\n177: │               ├── fake_codeinterpreter.go\n178: │               └── doc.go\n179: ├── informers/\n180: │   └── externalversions/\n181: │       ├── factory.go                 — SharedInformerFactory\n182: │       ├── generic.go                 — GenericInformer, ForResource\n183: │       ├── internalinterfaces/\n184: │       │   └── factory_interfaces.go  — NewInformerFunc, TweakListOptionsFunc\n185: │       └── runtime/\n186: │           ├── interface.go           — Group accessor\n187: │           └── v1alpha1/\n188: │               ├── interface.go       — v1alpha1 accessors\n189: │               ├── agentruntime.go    — AgentRuntime informer\n190: │               └── codeinterpreter.go — CodeInterpreter informer\n191: └── listers/\n192:     └── runtime/v1alpha1/\n193:         ├── agentruntime.go            — AgentRuntimeLister\n194:         ├── codeinterpreter.go         — CodeInterpreterLister\n195:         └── expansion_generated.go\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n199: \n200: #### CLI Toolkit\n201: \n202: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n203: |------------|---------|---------|\n204: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n205: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n206: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump |\n207: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | Async HTTP for invoke |\n208: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n209: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, tables, colored output |\n210: | `packaging` | `>=23.0` | Version detection |\n211: | `importlib-resources` | `>=6.0.0` | Template access |\n212: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic version handling |\n213: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client (optional, k8s extra) |\n214: \n215: #### Python SDK\n216: \n217: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n218: |------------|---------|---------|\n219: | `requests` | — | HTTP client |\n220: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT handling |\n221: | `cryptography` | — | Crypto primitives |\n222: \n223: #### client-go\n224: \n225: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n226: |------------|---------|---------|\n227: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes Go client |\n228: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | Code generation |\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ## 2. Data Structures\n233: \n234: ### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n235: \n236: Canonical metadata model persisted as `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n237: \n238: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n239: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n240: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n241: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n242: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n243: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n244: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n245: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n246: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n247: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n248: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n249: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n250: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n251: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n252: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n253: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n254: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n255: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n256: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n257: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n258: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n259: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n260: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n261: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n262: \n263: **Validators:**\n264: - `validate_language` → must be in `['python', 'java']` (lowercased)\n265: - `validate_build_mode` → must be in `['local', 'cloud']` (lowercased)\n266: - `validate_port` → must be in range `1..65535`\n267: \n268: ### 2.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n269: \n270: CLI option parsing intermediate structure.\n271: \n272: | Field | Type | Default |\n273: |-------|------|---------|\n274: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n275: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n276: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n277: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n278: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n279: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n280: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n281: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n282: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n283: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n284: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n285: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n286: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n287: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n288: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n289: \n290: **Classmethod:** `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\"`\n291: \n292: ### 2.3 Runtime Classes\n293: \n294: #### PackRuntime\n295: \n296: ```python\n297: class PackRuntime:\n298:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n299:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n300:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n301:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n302:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n303:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n304:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n305:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n306:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n307:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n308:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n309:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n310:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n311:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n312:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n313:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n314:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n315: ```\n316: \n317: #### BuildRuntime\n318: \n319: ```python\n320: class BuildRuntime:\n321:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n322:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n323:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n324:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n325:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n326:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n327:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n328: ```\n329: \n330: #### PublishRuntime\n331: \n332: ```python\n333: class PublishRuntime:\n334:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n335:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n336:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n337:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n338:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n339:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n340:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n341:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n342: ```\n343: \n344: #### InvokeRuntime\n345: \n346: ```python\n347: class InvokeRuntime:\n348:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n349:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n350:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n351:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n352:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Known issue:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if false, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`.\n356: \n357: #### StatusRuntime\n358: \n359: ```python\n360: class StatusRuntime:\n361:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n362:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n363:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n364:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ### 2.4 Service Classes\n368: \n369: #### DockerService\n370: \n371: ```python\n372: class DockerService:\n373:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n374:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n375:     def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n376:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n377:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n378:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n379:     def push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n380:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n381:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n382:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n383: ```\n384: \n385: #### MetadataService\n386: \n387: ```python\n388: class MetadataService:\n389:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n390:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n391:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n392:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n393:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n394:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n395:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n396: ```\n397: \n398: #### KubernetesProvider\n399: \n400: ```python\n401: class KubernetesProvider:\n402:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n403:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n404:     def deploy_agent(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, replicas: int = 1, node_port: Optional[int] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n405:     def _create_deployment(self, name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str], replicas: int, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n406:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n407:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n408:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n409:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n410:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n411: ```\n412: \n413: #### AgentCubeProvider\n414: \n415: ```python\n416: class AgentCubeProvider:\n417:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n418:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n419:     def deploy_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n420:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n421:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n422: ```\n423: \n424: **CR API:** `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n425: \n426: ### 2.5 Python SDK Clients\n427: \n428: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n429: \n430: ```python\n431: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n432:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", ttl: int = 3600, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, auth_token: Optional[str] = None, verbose: bool = False, session_id: Optional[str] = None): ...\n433:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n434:     def __enter__(self): ...\n435:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n436:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n437:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n438:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n439:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n440:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n441:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n442:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n443: ```\n444: \n445: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n446: \n447: ```python\n448: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n449:     def __init__(self, agent_name: str, namespace: str = \"default\", router_url: Optional[str] = None, verbose: bool = False, session_id: Optional[str] = None, timeout: int = 120, connect_timeout: float = 5.0): ...\n450:     def __enter__(self): ...\n451:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n452:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n453:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n454: ```\n455: \n456: ### 2.6 Exception Hierarchy (Python SDK)\n457: \n458: ```python\n459: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n460:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n461:     pass\n462: \n463: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n464:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n465:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n466:         self.stderr = stderr\n467:         self.command = command\n468:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n469: \n470: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n471:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n472:     pass\n473: \n474: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n475:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n476:     pass\n477: ```\n478: \n479: ### 2.7 client-go Types\n480: \n481: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n482: \n483: - **Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n484: - **Version:** `v1alpha1`\n485: - **Plural:** `agentruntimes`\n486: - **Kind:** `AgentRuntime`\n487: \n488: #### Clientset Interface\n489: \n490: ```go\n491: type Interface interface {\n492:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n493:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: #### AgentRuntimeInterface\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n501:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n502:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n503:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n504:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n505:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n506:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n507:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n508:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n509:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n510:     AgentRuntimeExpansion\n511: }\n512: ```\n513: \n514: ---\n515: \n516: ## 3. API Contracts\n517: \n518: ### 3.1 CLI Commands\n519: \n520: #### Console Script Entry Point\n521: \n522: ```toml\n523: [project.scripts]\n524: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n525: ```\n526: \n527: Typer app: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n528: \n529: #### Root Callback\n530: \n531: ```python\n532: def main(\n533:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\", callback=version_callback, is_eager=True),\n534:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n535: ) -> None:\n536:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n537: ```\n538: \n539: **Behaviors:**\n540: - `--version`: prints `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup), exits via `typer.Exit()`\n541: - `--verbose`/`-v`: calls `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n542: \n543: #### pack Command\n544: \n545: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n546: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n547: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n548: | `--agent-name` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n549: | `--language` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n550: | `--entrypoint` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n551: | `--port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n552: | `--build-mode` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n553: | `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n554: | `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n555: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n556: \n557: **Success output:**\n558: ```\n559: ✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\n560:   Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n561:   Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n562: ```\n563: \n564: **Error handling:** prints `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red; if verbose, prints traceback; exits with code `1`.\n565: \n566: #### build Command\n567: \n568: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n569: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n570: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n571: | `--proxy` | `-p` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n572: | `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n573: | `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for build artifacts |\n574: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n575: \n576: **Behaviors:**\n577: - Local build: requires Docker running; raises `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if unavailable\n578: - Version increment: bumps `metadata.version` (patch for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1`, or fallback `{version}-1`); reverts on build failure\n579: - Tag derived from metadata version\n580: \n581: #### publish Command\n582: \n583: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n584: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n585: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n586: | `--version` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n587: | `--image-url` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n588: | `--image-username` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n589: | `--image-password` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n590: | `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n591: | `--region` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n592: | `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n593: | `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n594: | `--node-port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment |\n595: | `--replicas` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n596: | `--namespace` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n597: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n598: \n599: **AgentCube provider prerequisites:** metadata must contain `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`; otherwise raises `ValueError`.\n600: \n601: **Standard K8s publish flow:** calls `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updates metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure raises `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata.\n602: \n603: #### invoke Command\n604: \n605: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n606: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n607: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n608: | `--payload` | — | `str` | `\"{}\"` | JSON-formatted input passed to the agent |\n609: | `--header` | — | `Optional[List[str]]` | `None` | Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Repeatable. |\n610: | `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n611: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n612: \n613: **Behaviors:**\n614: - Invalid JSON payload: prints error in red, exits with code `1`\n615: - Invalid header format (no single `:` separator): prints expected `key:value` format, exits with code `1`\n616: - Session header: if metadata contains `session_id`, adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header\n617: - AgentRuntime CR URL rewrite: when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrites URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n618: \n619: #### status Command\n620: \n621: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n622: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n623: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n624: | `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n625: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n626: \n627: **Behaviors:**\n628: - Displays status in Rich `Table`\n629: - If `status == \"not_published\"` (no `agent_id`): prints guidance to publish first, exits with code `1`\n630: - If `status == \"error\"`: exits with code `1`\n631: \n632: ### 3.2 Metadata File Format\n633: \n634: **Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`  \n635: **Load fallbacks:** `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n636: \n637: **Save format:**\n638: ```yaml\n639: agent_name: my-agent\n640: language: python\n641: entrypoint: python main.py\n642: port: 8080\n643: build_mode: local\n644: # ... other fields, None values excluded\n645: ```\n646: \n647: Written with `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)` after `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`.\n648: \n649: ### 3.3 Workspace Validation Rules\n650: \n651: | Language | Requirement | Error if Missing |\n652: |----------|-------------|------------------|\n653: | Any | Directory exists | `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` |\n654: | Python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n655: | Java | `pom.xml` in workspace root | `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` |\n656: \n657: ### 3.4 Dockerfile Generation\n658: \n659: **When generated:** If no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace root.\n660: \n661: **Python Dockerfile template:**\n662: ```dockerfile\n663: FROM python:3.10-slim\n664: WORKDIR /app\n665: COPY requirements.txt .\n666: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n667: COPY . .\n668: EXPOSE {port}\n669: CMD {entrypoint}\n670: ```\n671: \n672: **Java Dockerfile template:**\n673: ```dockerfile\n674: FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\n675: WORKDIR /app\n676: COPY pom.xml .\n677: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n678: COPY src ./src\n679: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n680: \n681: FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\n682: WORKDIR /app\n683: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n684: EXPOSE {port}\n685: CMD {entrypoint}\n686: ```\n687: \n688: ### 3.5 Docker Integration\n689: \n690: | Operation | Behavior |\n691: |-----------|----------|\n692: | `build_image` | Tags `{image_name}:{tag}`, passes optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, returns `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time` |\n693: | `push_image` | Logs in if username+password provided, retags when needed, streams push logs, returns `pushed_image` and `push_time` |\n694: | `remove_image` | Returns `True` on success; logs warning and returns `False` on failure |\n695: | `check_docker_available` | Returns `True` if Docker daemon is running and accessible |\n696: \n697: ### 3.6 Kubernetes — Standard Provider\n698: \n699: | Operation | Behavior |\n700: |-----------|----------|\n701: | `deploy_agent` | Creates/patches Deployment + NodePort Service; returns `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}` |\n702: | `wait_for_deployment_ready` | Polls until ready or timeout (default 120s); raises `TimeoutError` on expiry |\n703: | `delete_agent` | Deletes Deployment + Service; ignores 404 on individual deletes; returns `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` |\n704: | `get_agent_status` | Returns pod status, replica counts, conditions |\n705: \n706: ### 3.7 Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n707: \n708: | Operation | Behavior |\n709: |-----------|----------|\n710: | `deploy_agent_runtime` | Creates/patches AgentRuntime CR; embeds `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from params or env when missing in `env_vars`; sets `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`; references `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]` |\n711: | `get_agent_runtime` | Returns CR object or `None` if not found |\n712: \n713: ### 3.8 Python SDK — Code Interpreter\n714: \n715: #### Control Plane HTTP\n716: \n717: | Method | Path | Notes |\n718: |--------|------|-------|\n719: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n720: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n721: \n722: **Headers:**\n723: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n724: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n725: \n726: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n727: \n728: #### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) — Base URL\n729: \n730: If `base_url` is not provided:\n731: ```text\n732: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n733: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n734: ```\n735: \n736: #### Data Plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n737: \n738: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n739: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n740: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n741: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n742: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n743: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n744: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n745: \n746: **Headers:**\n747: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n748: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set\n749: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n750: \n751: ### 3.9 Python SDK — Agent Runtime\n752: \n753: #### Data Plane — Base URL\n754: \n755: ```text\n756: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n757: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n758: ```\n759: \n760: #### Data Plane — HTTP\n761: \n762: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n763: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n764: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n765: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n766: \n767: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout` (default 120).\n768: \n769: ### 3.10 Configuration Resolution\n770: \n771: #### CLI Toolkit\n772: \n773: | Component | Resolved settings |\n774: |-----------|-------------------|\n775: | `KubernetesProvider` | `namespace` ← arg or `\"default\"`; `kubeconfig` ← arg or `$KUBECONFIG` or `~/.kube/config` |\n776: | `AgentCubeProvider` | Same as KubernetesProvider |\n777: | `DockerService` | Uses `docker.from_env()` (respects `$DOCKER_HOST`, `$DOCKER_CERT_PATH`) |\n778: \n779: #### Python SDK\n780: \n781: | Component | Resolved settings |\n782: |-----------|-------------------|\n783: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `$WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n784: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `$ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n785: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n786: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `$ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n787: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults as above |\n788: \n789: ### 3.11 Entrypoint Inference\n790: \n791: | Language | Inference Logic |\n792: |----------|-----------------|\n793: | Python | Find first `*.py` file in workspace root (alphabetically sorted); default to `python <file>` |\n794: | Java | Default to `java -jar app.jar` |\n795: \n796: If inference fails and no `--entrypoint` provided: raise `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")`.\n797: \n798: ### 3.12 Dependency Processing\n799: \n800: | Language | Detection | Action |\n801: |----------|-----------|--------|\n802: | Python | `requirements.txt` exists | Validate file is readable; set `requirements_file` in metadata |\n803: | Python | `requirements.txt` missing | Create empty file in workspace |\n804: | Java | `pom.xml` exists | Validate XML is parseable |\n805: | Java | `pom.xml` missing | Already caught by workspace validation |\n806: \n807: ---\n808: \n809: ## 4. Error Handling\n810: \n811: ### 4.1 CLI Error Handling Pattern\n812: \n813: ```python\n814: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n815:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n816:     if verbose:\n817:         console.print_exception()\n818:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n819: ```\n820: \n821: **Key behaviors:**\n822: - All subcommand exceptions flow through `_handle_error`\n823: - Subcommand's local `--verbose` flag controls traceback display (independent of global `-v`)\n824: - Exit code is always `1` on error\n825: \n826: ### 4.2 Sentinel Errors (CLI Toolkit)\n827: \n828: #### PackRuntime\n829: \n830: | Error | Condition |\n831: |-------|-----------|\n832: | `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` | Workspace path doesn't exist |\n833: | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` | Python language, no `*.py` files |\n834: | `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` | Java language, no `pom.xml` |\n835: | `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")` | Language not in `['python', 'java']` |\n836: | `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")` | No entrypoint and inference failed |\n837: | `RuntimeError(\"Failed to generate Dockerfile: {reason}\")` | Dockerfile generation failure |\n838: \n839: #### BuildRuntime\n840: \n841: | Error | Condition |\n842: |-------|-----------|\n843: | `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` | Docker daemon unavailable in local build mode |\n844: \n845: #### PublishRuntime\n846: \n847: | Error | Condition |\n848: |-------|-----------|\n849: | `ValueError` (message requiring `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`) | AgentCube provider, metadata lacks required URLs |\n850: | `RuntimeError` (after recording error in metadata) | Deployment readiness check failed |\n851: \n852: #### InvokeRuntime\n853: \n854: | Error | Condition |\n855: |-------|-----------|\n856: | `json.JSONDecodeError` | Invalid payload JSON |\n857: | `ValueError` (expected `key:value` format) | Invalid header format |\n858: | `UnboundLocalError` (known bug) | `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with non-HTTP endpoint |\n859: \n860: #### StatusRuntime\n861: \n862: | Error | Condition |\n863: |-------|-----------|\n864: | `typer.Exit(1)` | Status is `not_published` or `error` |\n865: \n866: ### 4.3 Python SDK Error Handling\n867: \n868: | Exception | Raised When |\n869: |-----------|-------------|\n870: | `ValueError` | Router URL missing, session_id not initialized, missing response header |\n871: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n872: | `AgentCubeError` | Base class for all SDK errors |\n873: | `SessionError` | Session creation or management failure (defined, not currently raised) |\n874: | `DataPlaneError` | Data plane operation failure (defined, not currently raised) |\n875: | `requests` exceptions | Network-level failures |\n876: \n877: #### Context Manager Cleanup\n878: \n879: **CodeInterpreterClient:**\n880: - `__exit__` calls `stop()` → closes data-plane session, deletes control-plane session if `session_id` was set, closes control plane HTTP session\n881: - Data plane init failure after session create: logs warning, calls `delete_session(session_id)`, sets `session_id` to `None`, re-raises\n882: \n883: **AgentRuntimeClient:**\n884: - `__exit__` calls `close()` → closes underlying `requests.Session`\n885: \n886: ### 4.4 Timeout Behavior\n887: \n888: | Component | Default Read Timeout | Default Connect Timeout |\n889: |-----------|---------------------|------------------------|\n890: | ControlPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n891: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n892: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n893: | `execute_command` | `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (buffer to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124) | 5.0s |\n894: \n895: ---\n896: \n897: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n898: \n899: ### 5.1 CLI Toolkit Tests\n900: \n901: #### PackRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_pack_runtime.py`)\n902: \n903: | Test Name | Description |\n904: |-----------|-------------|\n905: | `TestPackRuntime_ValidPythonWorkspace` | Valid Python workspace with `main.py` → packs successfully |\n906: | `TestPackRuntime_ValidJavaWorkspace` | Valid Java workspace with `pom.xml` → packs successfully |\n907: | `TestPackRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n908: | `TestPackRuntime_NoPythonFiles` | Python language, no `*.py` → `ValueError(\"No Python files found\")` |\n909: | `TestPackRuntime_NoPomXml` | Java language, no `pom.xml` → `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found\")` |\n910: | `TestPackRuntime_UnsupportedLanguage` | `language=ruby` → `ValueError(\"Unsupported language\")` |\n911: | `TestPackRuntime_ExistingMetadata` | `agent_metadata.yaml` present → loads and merges |\n912: | `TestPackRuntime_FallbackMetadata` | Only `agent.yaml` present → loads from fallback |\n913: | `TestPackRuntime_NoMetadata` | No metadata files → creates new from options |\n914: | `TestPackRuntime_CliOverrides` | CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata |\n915: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointPython` | No entrypoint, Python workspace → infers `python main.py` |\n916: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointJava` | No entrypoint, Java workspace → infers `java -jar app.jar` |\n917: | `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointFails` | No `*.py` files, no entrypoint → `ValueError` |\n918: | `TestPackRuntime_GeneratePythonDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Python → generates correct Dockerfile |\n919: | `TestPackRuntime_GenerateJavaDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Java → generates correct Dockerfile |\n920: | `TestPackRuntime_ExistingDockerfile` | Dockerfile exists → not regenerated |\n921: | `TestPackRuntime_CreateRequirementsTxt` | Python workspace without `requirements.txt` → creates empty file |\n922: | `TestPackRuntime_OutputPath` | `--output` specified → returns output path, not workspace |\n923: | `TestPackRuntime_MetadataSavedCorrectly` | Metadata file written with correct YAML format |\n924: | `TestPackRuntime_PortValidation` | `--port=0` → Pydantic validation error |\n925: | `TestPackRuntime_PortValidationHigh` | `--port=70000` → Pydantic validation error |\n926: \n927: #### BuildRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_build_runtime.py`)\n928: \n929: | Test Name | Description |\n930: |-----------|-------------|\n931: | `TestBuildRuntime_LocalBuildSuccess` | Local Docker build succeeds |\n932: | `TestBuildRuntime_DockerUnavailable` | Docker unavailable → `RuntimeError` |\n933: | `TestBuildRuntime_VersionIncrement` | Version bumped on successful build |\n934: | `TestBuildRuntime_VersionRevertOnFailure` | Version reverted on build failure |\n935: | `TestBuildRuntime_CloudBuild` | Cloud build mode delegates correctly |\n936: | `TestBuildRuntime_ProxySettings` | Proxy passed as build args |\n937: \n938: #### PublishRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py`)\n939: \n940: | Test Name | Description |\n941: |-----------|-------------|\n942: | `TestPublishRuntime_AgentCubeProvider` | Publish to AgentRuntime CR |\n943: | `TestPublishRuntime_K8sProvider` | Publish to Deployment + Service |\n944: | `TestPublishRuntime_MissingUrls` | AgentCube provider without required URLs → `ValueError` |\n945: | `TestPublishRuntime_ReadinessTimeout` | Deployment not ready → `RuntimeError` |\n946: | `TestPublishRuntime_LocalImagePrep` | Prepare local image for publishing |\n947: | `TestPublishRuntime_CloudImagePrep` | Prepare cloud image for publishing |\n948: \n949: #### InvokeRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`)\n950: \n951: | Test Name | Description |\n952: |-----------|-------------|\n953: | `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidPayload` | Valid JSON payload → successful invoke |\n954: | `TestInvokeRuntime_InvalidPayload` | Invalid JSON → error, exit 1 |\n955: | `TestInvokeRuntime_InvalidHeader` | Bad header format → error, exit 1 |\n956: | `TestInvokeRuntime_SessionHeader` | `session_id` in metadata → `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header added |\n957: | `TestInvokeRuntime_AgentCubeUrlRewrite` | AgentRuntime CR → URL rewritten to invocation path |\n958: | `TestInvokeRuntime_DirectHttpInvocation` | Standard K8s → direct POST to endpoint |\n959: \n960: #### StatusRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`)\n961: \n962: | Test Name | Description |\n963: |-----------|-------------|\n964: | `TestStatusRuntime_NotPublished` | No `agent_id` → guidance to publish, exit 1 |\n965: | `TestStatusRuntime_CrStatus` | AgentRuntime CR status read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` |\n966: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sStatus` | Standard K8s deployment status |\n967: | `TestStatusRuntime_ErrorStatus` | Error status → exit 1 |\n968: \n969: #### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_commands.py`)\n970: \n971: | Test Name | Description |\n972: |-----------|-------------|\n973: | `TestCli_VersionFlag` | `--version` → prints version, exits |\n974: | `TestCli_VerboseLogging` | `-v` → DEBUG logging enabled |\n975: | `TestCli_PackCommand` | `pack` command integration |\n976: | `TestCli_BuildCommand` | `build` command integration |\n977: | `TestCli_PublishCommand` | `publish` command integration |\n978: | `TestCli_InvokeCommand` | `invoke` command integration |\n979: | `TestCli_StatusCommand` | `status` command integration |\n980: | `TestCli_HandleErrorVerbose` | Error + verbose → traceback printed |\n981: | `TestCli_HandleErrorQuiet` | Error, no verbose → message only |\n982: \n983: #### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n984: \n985: | Test Name | Description |\n986: |-----------|-------------|\n987: | `TestMetadataService_SaveAndLoad` | Save → load round-trip preserves fields |\n988: | `TestMetadataService_FallbackLoad` | `agent.yaml` present, `agent_metadata.yaml` absent → loads fallback |\n989: | `TestMetadataService_ExcludeNone` | `None` fields excluded from YAML output |\n990: | `TestMetadataService_YamlFormat` | Output uses `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, `default_flow_style=False` |\n991: | `TestMetadataService_ValidatePythonWorkspace` | Python workspace validation |\n992: | `TestMetadataService_ValidateJavaWorkspace` | Java workspace validation |\n993: \n994: #### DockerService Tests (`tests/services/test_docker_service.py`)\n995: \n996: | Test Name | Description |\n997: |-----------|-------------|\n998: | `TestDockerService_BuildImage` | Build image with tag and build args |\n999: | `TestDockerService_PushImage` | Push with login and retag |\n1000: | `TestDockerService_RemoveImage` | Remove image success and failure |\n1001: | `TestDockerService_CheckAvailable` | Docker availability check |\n1002: \n1003: #### KubernetesProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n1004: \n1005: | Test Name | Description |\n1006: |-----------|-------------|\n1007: | `TestK8sProvider_DeployAgent` | Deploy Deployment + Service |\n1008: | `TestK8sProvider_WaitForReady` | Wait for deployment ready |\n1009: | `TestK8sProvider_WaitTimeout` | Timeout exceeded → `TimeoutError` |\n1010: | `TestK8sProvider_DeleteAgent` | Delete agent, ignore 404 |\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1010. Use offset=1011 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe K8s/AgentCube Provider delivers a complete developer toolchain for AI agent lifecycle management on Kubernetes. It consists of three components:\n\n1. **CLI Toolkit** (`kubectl-agentcube`) — Command-line interface for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube CRDs or standard Kubernetes deployments.\n2. **Client-Go Library** — Generated Kubernetes typed client for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n3. **Python SDK** (`agentcube-sdk`) — High-level Python client library for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 System Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          Developer Workstation                           │\n│                                                                          │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  CLI Toolkit     │  │   Python SDK     │  │    client-go (Go)     │  │","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775864045737,"end":1775864045748}}}}
