{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864152731,"sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","part":{"id":"prt_d79bf09f5001aqfOtPCuMZxee9","messageID":"msg_d79bee0f1001QtNoD7AdFNhsJZ","sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the design.md for AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient:","time":{"start":1775864152729,"end":1775864152729}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864152739,"sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","part":{"id":"prt_d79bf0b0d001AKxqD2fXtUEUy4","messageID":"msg_d79bee0f1001QtNoD7AdFNhsJZ","sessionID":"ses_28642a5d7ffeQl9JUpSelqfkoR","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_3d6d2ff19bd34983b5265574","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) provides a high-level client library for:\n\n1. **Code Interpreter Sessions** — Create/manage sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n2. **Agent Runtime Invocation** — Bootstrap sessions and invoke agent workloads through the Router.\n\n### 1.2 Layered Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public Client Layer                      │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient  │  AgentRuntimeClient               │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                  Data Plane Clients                         │\n│  CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient  │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                  Control Plane Client                       │\n│                     ControlPlaneClient                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                    HTTP Utilities                           │\n│  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Design Principles\n\n- **No single Configuration class** — Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across components.\n- **Context manager support** — All public clients implement `__enter__`/`__exit__` for resource cleanup.\n- **Session header management** — `x-agentcube-session-id` (lowercase) is used consistently for Router requests.\n- **Timeout safety** — Execute command adds +2.0s buffer to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n\n### 1.4 Package Layout\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Package agentcube-sdk, dependencies\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py            — CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py               — AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                  — Exception classes\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports client classes\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py           — ControlPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Empty (module marker)\n│       ├── http.py                    — create_session\n│       ├── utils.py                   — read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                     — get_logger\n├── examples/\n│   ├── basic_usage.py                 — CodeInterpreterClient usage examples\n│   └── agent_runtime_usage.py         — AgentRuntimeClient usage examples\n├── scripts/\n│   └── e2e_picod_test.py              — End-to-end test against PicoD\n└── tests/\n    └── *.py                           — Unit and integration tests\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n```\n\n- `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n- Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n- Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentExecutionError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n**Note:** `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules. Callers may rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n\n### 2.2 `CodeInterpreterClient` Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | Session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `ttl` | `int` | Session TTL in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Logger instance |\n| `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Active session ID |\n| `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client |\n\n### 2.3 `AgentRuntimeClient` Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Agent runtime name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default read timeout (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connect timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Logger instance |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Active session ID |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client |\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Public Exports\n\n#### `agentcube/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n#### `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n\n```python\nfrom .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n### 3.2 `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    )\n\n    def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n    def stop(self) -> None\n    def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n```\n\n#### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Setting | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| `router_url` | Argument or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| `auth_token` | Argument or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n| `name` | Argument (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n| `namespace` | Argument (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `ttl` | Argument (default: `3600`) |\n| `session_id` | Argument (optional; if provided, skips session creation) |\n\n#### Lifecycle\n\n1. **Init:** Resolve `router_url` → raise `ValueError` if missing. Create `ControlPlaneClient`. If `session_id` is `None`, call `create_session()`. Call `_init_data_plane()`.\n2. **Data plane init failure:** If `_init_data_plane()` raises after session creation, log warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id = None`, re-raise.\n3. **Context manager exit:** Call `stop()` → close data plane session, delete control plane session (if `session_id` set), close control plane HTTP session.\n\n### 3.3 `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    )\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### Lifecycle\n\n1. **Init:** Resolve `router_url`. Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`. If `session_id` is `None`, call `bootstrap_session_id()` via `GET` on invocation base URL. Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header; if missing, raise `ValueError`.\n2. **Invoke:** If `session_id` is falsy, raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`.\n3. **Context manager exit:** Call `close()` → close underlying `requests.Session`.\n\n### 3.4 `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Body / Notes |\n|--------|------|--------------|\n| `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON: `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` → returns `data[\"sessionId\"]` |\n| `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success (returns `True`) |\n\n#### Headers\n\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n\n#### Timeout\n\n`(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n\n### 3.5 `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response\n    def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### Base URL Resolution\n\nIf `base_url` is not provided:\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n\n| Method | Relative Path | Body / Params |\n|--------|---------------|---------------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | Query `path` |\n\n#### Headers\n\n- Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n\n**Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n\n#### Timeout Behavior\n\n`execute_command` adds +2.0s buffer to read timeout to avoid premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124.\n\n### 3.6 `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str\n    def invoke(self, session_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> requests.Response\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n#### Base URL\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n#### Timeouts\n\n`(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` is method argument or `self.timeout`.\n\n### 3.7 Utility Functions\n\n#### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n```\n\nMounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n\n#### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n```\n\nReturns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n\n#### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Summary\n\n| Component | Resolved Settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults as above |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Exception Flow\n\n```\nAgentCubeError (base)\n├── CommandExecutionError  ← execute_command with exit_code != 0\n├── SessionError           ← session creation/management failures (defined, not raised)\n└── DataPlaneError         ← data plane operation failures (defined, not raised)\n```\n\n### 5.2 Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Behavior |\n|----------|----------|\n| Command non-zero exit | Raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` |\n| Router URL missing | Raise `ValueError` in `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n| Session bootstrap header missing | Raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n| Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` |\n| Delete session 404 | Return `True` (treated as success) |\n| Delete session other failure | Log and return `False` |\n| Data plane init failure after session create | Log warning, delete session, set `session_id=None`, re-raise |\n\n### 5.3 Timeout Behavior\n\n| Component | Default Read Timeout | Default Connect Timeout |\n|-----------|---------------------|------------------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| `execute_command` | `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (buffer to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124) | 5.0s |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n\n### 6.1 Python Code Execution Path\n\nWhen `run_code` is called with `language` in `[\"python\", \"py\", \"python3\"]`:\n\n1. Generate timestamped filename: `f\"/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py\"`\n2. Write code content via `write_file`\n3. Execute via `execute_command(f\"python3 {filename}\", timeout=timeout)`\n\n### 6.2 Session Header Consistency\n\nAll Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- Multipart uploads: Explicitly set on POST request (no JSON Content-Type)\n\n### 6.3 Timeout Buffer Logic\n\nFor `execute_command`:\n\n```python\ntimeout_value = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout  # default 120\npico_timeout_str = f\"{timeout_value}s\"\nread_timeout = timeout_value + 2.0  # buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope |\n|----------|-------|\n| Unit tests | Individual client methods, mock HTTP responses |\n| Integration tests | Control plane + data plane interaction (mocked servers) |\n| E2E tests | Real environment with `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n\n### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_ContextManagerCleanup` | `__exit__` calls `stop()`, closes sessions |\n| `TestDataPlaneInitFailure_RollbackSession` | Data plane init failure rolls back session |\n| `TestRouterUrlRequired_MissingEnv` | Missing `router_url` and `ROUTER_URL` → `ValueError` |\n\n#### Command Execution\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestExecuteCommand_NonZeroExit` | Non-zero exit raises `CommandExecutionError` |\n| `TestRunCode_PythonExecution` | Python code writes timestamped `.py` file and runs `python3` |\n| `TestExecuteCommand_TimeoutBuffer` | Timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied correctly |\n\n#### File Operations\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestWriteFile_Base64Content` | `write_file` sends base64 content with mode `0644` |\n| `TestUploadFile_MultipartSessionHeader` | `upload_file` sends multipart with session header |\n| `TestDownloadFile_StreamResponse` | `download_file` streams response |\n| `TestListFiles_QueryPath` | `list_files` queries with path parameter |\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_BootstrapSessionId` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeWithoutSession` | Invoke validates session ID presence |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_ContextManagerClosesSession` | Context manager closes HTTP session |\n\n#### Control Plane\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_CreateSession` | Create session returns `sessionId` |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_DeleteSession404` | Delete session handles 404 gracefully |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_AuthTokenFromSAFile` | Auth token resolution from SA file |\n\n#### Timeout Behavior\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestExecuteCommand_DefaultTimeout` | Default timeouts (120s read, 5.0s connect) |\n| `TestExecuteCommand_PerCallOverride` | Per-call override for execute_command |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeTimeoutTuple` | AgentRuntimeClient invoke timeout tuple |\n\n### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n\n- Use `unittest.mock` or `pytest-mock` for `requests.Session`\n- Mock `create_session` to return controlled `requests.Session` instances\n- Use `responses` library or custom adapters for HTTP endpoint mocking\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775864152554,"end":1775864152736}}}}
